Beyonics, China Sports, First Ship: Singapore Stocks Preview

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 
2011-06-05T23:43:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/beyonics-china-sports-first-ship-singapore-stocks-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes in  Singapore  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and share prices are from the previous close.  Singapore’s  Straits Times Index (FSSTI)  dropped 0.5 percent to
3,145.67.  Beyonics Technology Ltd. (BT)  : The provider of
electronics manufacturing services said it expects to post a
loss in the third-quarter ended April 30 due to lower demand in
the hard-disk-drive industry. The stock was unchanged at 18
Singapore cents.  China Sports International Ltd. (CSPORT)  : The maker of
sports footwear and apparel said it agreed to buy a 10 percent
stake in Jinjiang Guosheng Shoe Material Co., a supplier of
soles to global shoe brands such as Fila and Reebok, for 45
million yuan ($6.9 million). China Sports slumped 12 percent to
7.5 Singapore cents.  First Ship Lease Trust (FSLT)  : The Singapore-based ship
leasing company had its credit rating outlook raised to
“stable” from “negative” at  Fitch Ratings , saying it
believes credit quality has stabilized. First Ship was unchanged
at 38 Singapore cents.  Novo Group Ltd. (NOVO SP): The Singapore-based steel
supplier said it expects to report “significantly lower” net
income for the year ended April 30 due to decreased profit
margins. The stock slumped 8.6 percent to 32 Singapore cents
when it last traded on June 2.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Burgos in Singapore at 
 jburgos4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at   ngentle2@bloomberg.net . 